to the editor re regulators ease rules governing media ownership front page june 3 the substance of the federal communications commission decision has properly received a great deal of attention what has been overlooked is the desirability in a democratic country of purely political decisions like this one being made by an appointed regulatory body rather than by congress decision making by the fcc should be confined to issues that are technological purely political decisions should be moved to congress in addition the fcc should have as commissioners those who have adequate professional backgrounds in their fields of work william f schreiber cambridge mass june 3 2003 the writer is former director of the mit advanced television research program

